<P>
WENDELL O. HENDERSON; PRESIDENT OF CONSOLIDATED REALTY BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wendell O. Henderson, 65, real estate businessman who served two terms as 
president of the Consolidated Realty Board.The owner of Exclusive Properties 
Real Estate, Henderson also served as a second vice president of the National 
Assn. of Real Estate Brokers. Born in Texas, he moved to Los Angeles with his 
family as a teen-ager and studied architecture at USC and UCLA. Henderson began 
his career in retail sales with Beverly Hills Silk and Woolens and switched to 
realty sales with W.A. Robinson Real Estate. After earning his broker's 
license, he founded his own firm, which eventually employed 37 agents. On April 
9 in Los Angeles after a long illness. 
