 Soccer 
</P>
<P>
 The United States will play Saudi Arabia in an exhibition game May 25 in 
Piscataway, N.J., in a World Cup tuneup for both teams.The game at Rutgers 
Stadium will be the second in a three-game East Coast swing for the U.S. team 
</P>
<P>
 The Americans play Bayern Munich of Germany on May 21 at Cleveland Stadium. 
After the Saudi game, the United States plays Greece on May 28 at the Yale Bowl 
in New Haven, Conn. Miscellany 
</P>
<P>
 Christa Gannon, a women's basketball player at Santa Barbara, and Randal 
Pinkett, a track athlete at Rutgers, were selected for this year's NCAA Walter 
Byers Scholarships, worth $10,000 each. 
