BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Underfunding of Pension Program Up 39.5% in a Year: The Pension Benefit 
Guaranty Corp. said its pension protection program was underfunded by $53 
billion at the end of 1992, the most recent year for which figures are 
available.That's up 39.5% from the $38-billion shortfall at the end of 1991, 
according to the PBGC's annual report to Congress. The $53-billion shortfall 
for 1992, first reported in January, is the result of the PBGC's attempt to 
cover $11.3 billion of liabilities for pension payments with just $8.4 billion 
in its fund. While the PBGC has money to cover pensions under financially 
troubled plans now, it will run into trouble later unless the fund receives 
more money. 
