<P>
 Hamburger Hamlet Chief Resigns: Hamburger Hamlet Restaurants Inc. said 
Chairman and Chief Executive Thomas A. McFall resigned as part of an agreement 
with a major shareholder group. The faction, HAMB Investors Group, last month 
indicated it might seek McFall's resignation as part of a plan to try to 
improve earnings at the Sherman Oaks-based company.HAMB Investors owns 16.2% of 
Hamburger Hamlet, which operates 23 restaurants in California and 14 in other 
parts of the nation. The company said its directors elected fellow board member 
James J. Gaffney to replace McFall as chairman. Gaffney is chief operating 
officer of KDI Industries, a Cincinnati-based manufacturer of swimming pools 
and electronic components for military weapons systems. Another board member, 
Jack A. Lavine, was selected for the post of chief executive. Lavine founded 
the Chili's restaurant chain. 
