</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Multimedia: In a deal that reflects the evolution of interactive 
entertainment, Los Angeles-based Activision has signed an agreement with 
"Demolition Man" co-screenwriter Peter Lenkov to write and develop a new series 
of CD-ROM computer and video games.Lenkov plans to create a futuristic "cyber 
universe" with characters and stories that may later be adapted to TV and film. 
As new technology has transformed games that were once crude and jerky into 
something more aesthetically akin to interactive movies, with highly realistic 
animation and live-action video, the evolution in plot and character has for 
the most part lagged behind. Now multimedia developers are beginning to turn to 
Hollywood writers to supply more sophisticated stories to match the technology. 
AMY HARMON 
