<P>
ALL GEARED UP FOR THEIR WORKOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What do you wear to a Sweat-A-Thon? 
</P>
<P>
 Absorbent aerobic wear and a headband, as did many of the 125 exercise 
enthusiasts who participated in a three-hour fitness marathon at Orange Coast 
College in Costa Mesa on Saturday to raise funds for AIDS research and patient 
care. 
</P>
<P>
 The event was part of the City of Hope National Medical Center's annual 
fund-raiser that draws thousands of people to 120 sites around the nation to 
"Workout for Hope" and raise $2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Orange Coast College gymnasium, participants labored over back-to-back 
15-minute aerobic programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Many of the mostly female crowd dressed in a practical way to keep cool: 
shorts, tank tops and headbands. 
</P>
<P>
 Others, however, chose wild, fun outfits: peekaboo leotards, matching printed 
outfits for the layered look, and bikini briefs over bicycle shorts. 
</P>
