<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: LA CRESCENTA; BOY, 9, DIES AFTER BEING HIT WITH BALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC MALNIC 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 9-year-old La Crescenta boy -- who played three more innings after being 
struck in the head with a baseball -- collapsed and died several hours after 
the game, officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 An autopsy was scheduled to determine the cause of Timothy Richard Herman's 
death. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's Lt. Ralph Martin, a friend of the family and a baseball manager in 
the Crescenta Sports Assn. league, said the boy's parents, Robert and Karen 
Herman, doubted that the impact of the ball caused Timothy's death. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials said Timothy was wearing a batting helmet when he was struck in the 
head by a pitched ball Wednesday evening. 
</P>
<P>
 "It glanced off his helmet," Martin said. "He hardly felt it. He ran to first 
base, and then pitched three more innings." 
</P>
<P>
 About three hours later, Timothy complained of pain in his right leg and 
collapsed, officials said. He was rushed to Verdugo Hills Hospital, where he 
was pronounced dead about 11:45 p.m. ERIC MALNIC 
</P>
</TEXT>
