SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; 1 KILLED IN FIRE AT ROADSIDE HOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 One person was killed in a Thursday afternoon fire that destroyed one room and 
damaged five others at a roadside hotel across from Magic Mountain amusement 
park, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The unidentified victim is described as a male of unknown age whose body was 
badly burned in the blaze, which broke out shortly after 2 p.m. on the first 
floor of the Ranch House Inn in the 27400 block of Tourney Road, said Inspector 
Mario DeFina of the Los Angeles County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 About 30 firefighters battled the blaze at the two-story structure for about 
20 minutes before bringing it under control, DeFina said. 
</P>
<P>
 Damage was estimated at $140,000. 
</P>
<P>
 The cause of the fire is being investigated by arson investigators from the 
County Fire Department and the Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department, DeFina 
said. 
