<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; RANGERS RAISE RAILS AFTER WOMAN 
FALLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Texas Rangers raised the right-field upper deck railings at the Ballpark 
in Arlington before Thursday's game against Milwaukee in response to an 
opening-day accident. 
</P>
<P>
 The railings were elevated from 30 1/4 inches to 42 inches by using temporary 
rails.The new permanent railings will be 46 inches tall. 
</P>
<P>
 After Monday's home opener, 27-year-old Holly Minter of Plano, Tex., fell from 
the original lower railing while posing for a photo. Minter fell 30 feet to the 
lower deck, breaking three ribs and an arm. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 San Francisco Giant coach Bobby Bonds, the father of Barry Bonds, was 
hospitalized after suffering chest pains during a game with the Atlanta Braves. 
He was held overnight at Piedmont Hospital in Atlanta for precautionary tests. 
</P>
