</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Home Theater Products International: The company said Thursday that it has 
acquired a $7-million working capital line of credit with Bank of America at an 
interest rate of prime plus half a percentage point.That is greatly improved 
from its previous line of credit, the company said. The change will help it 
save about 8 cents per share each year, the Anaheim-based company said. Home 
Theater makes and sells consumer electronics, especially audio and video 
products. 
</P>
