<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: AUTOMOBILES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by John O'Dell, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Off-Track Enterprise: Four-time Indianapolis 500 winner Al Unser won't be 
spending much time in Long Beach watching the Indy-car races this weekend -- 
he'll be at the grand opening of the Al Unser Auto Care Center on Beach 
Boulevard in Huntington Beach from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. today, Saturday and 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Unser has joined with financial partner Robert Smith to launch what they hope 
will become a chain of Unser centers. The inaugural location here is a 
40,000-square-foot facility subdivided into quick-lube, brake, muffler, smog 
inspection and wheel alignment shops plus repair centers for domestic, Japanese 
and European cars. 
