<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; STATE DESIGNATES RECYCLING ZONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The state Integrated Waste Management Board recently designated Anaheim Canyon 
Business Center as a recycling market development zone. 
</P>
<P>
 The designation entitles businesses within the 2,400-acre area to low-interest 
loans and other state assistance. The businesses manufacture products from 
recycled materials such as glass, plastic and paper. 
</P>
<P>
 The business center contains the largest material-recovery facility by volume 
in the Western United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
