<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; OPEN ENROLLMENT BEGINS MONDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Parents of the Westminster School District may apply to send their children to 
any district school during the open enrollment period from Monday to April 29, 
a spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications are available at all district schools. 
</P>
<P>
 To apply, parents must fill out the form and have it signed by principals at 
both the home school and the new school. Forms should be returned to the 
student's home school. Parents will be notified by May 13 whether the request 
has been approved, said district spokeswoman Audrey Brown. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is an opportunity that many of our parents still don't know about or 
understand," said Assistant Supt. Barbara Fileto. 
</P>
<P>
 She said the program "gives great flexibility to parents who, for example, may 
need to find a school near their day care provider."JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
