<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; REGISTRATION FOR KINDERGARTEN BEGINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Parents of children who will be 5 years old by Dec. 1 and who will attend 
school in the Santa Ana Unified School District should register their children 
now for the upcoming school year, district officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Proof of the child's age, such as a birth or baptism certificate, is required 
for registration. Also, proof of immunization for polio, diphtheria, measles, 
mumps and rubella is required, district spokeswoman Diane Thomas said. 
</P>
<P>
 For kindergarten registration times or additional information, parents should 
contact their local school or the district's elementary division at (714) 
558-5523.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
