<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; MAN IS ARRESTED IN THEFTS AT PRESCHOOLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies have arrested a Tustin man on suspicion of stealing purses 
and wallets from cars of parents dropping off their children at South County 
preschools. 
</P>
<P>
 Alvaro Sosa Lizarraga, 25, was arrested Wednesday at a Tustin fast food 
restaurant.At the time, Lizarraga was with his 2-year-old son, who police said 
was used to help Lizarraga blend in to the preschool crowds. 
</P>
<P>
 "It really bothered us that he was using his child," said Lt. Dan Martini. 
</P>
<P>
 Lizarraga was being held on $10,000 bond at the Orange County Jail on 
suspicion of theft. The child was placed in his mother's custody. 
</P>
<P>
 "Evidently, his wife had no idea this was going on," Martini said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police contend that, since December, Lizarraga went to at least 10 preschools 
in Mission Viejo, Lake Forest and Laguna Hills. While parents, mostly mothers, 
dropped off their children, Lizarraga allegedly entered their unoccupied 
vehicles and took purses and wallets, removing cash before discarding them near 
the schools, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses' descriptions led deputies to Lizarraga and his son, Martini said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
