<P>
SOFTBALL ROUNDUP; VILLA PARK, MCARTHUR BEAT FOOTHILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Villa Park softball Coach Dave Shelton is happy his Spartans had 16 games to 
prepare for the Century League race. 
</P>
<P>
 "Our girls finally learned how to bunt properly and because of it we are 2-0 
in league," Shelton said Thursday after two sacrifice bunts set up the only run 
of the game against Foothill. 
</P>
<P>
 Heather Culver singled home Julie Riley with one out in the seventh inning to 
give Villa Park a 1-0 victory. The Spartans are 11-7, 2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Riley opened the bottom of the seventh with a single down the left-field line. 
Tammy Kincaid was safe when her bunt was mishandled. Silvia Salgado's bunt 
traveled less than a foot, but it was enough to move both runners over. Culver 
then singled to left center. 
</P>
<P>
 Brandee McArthur (6-3) pitched a two-hitter but had to survive a shaky first 
inning. Foothill (13-6, 1-1) loaded the bases when Laureen Bayer was safe on a 
passed ball after a strikeout and Gieron and Amie Barnes walked. McArthur 
struck out the next batter -- her third strikeout of the inning -- to end the 
threat. 
</P>
<P>
 McArthur helped herself by catching a line drive and turning it into a double 
play in the second inning. Only one Foothill runner reached base -- on a walk 
-- in the final five innings. MIKE WOJCIECHOWSKI 
