<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESEDA HIGH'S GALAN ACCEPTS CSUN VOLLEYBALL SCHOLARSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pat Galan, a 6-foot-4 outside hitter from Reseda High, has accepted a 
scholarship to play volleyball at Cal State Northridge, his father said 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Galan is the first Reseda player to sign with the Matadors since middle 
blocker Coley Kyman chose to play for Northridge in 1990. Kyman became a 
three-time All-American. 
</P>
<P>
 Galan, who took up volleyball as a sophomore, was a second-team All-City 
selection last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Justin Hamilton, from Clovis High in Fresno, said he also has signed with 
Northridge. Hamilton, a 6-6 left-hander, has been converted from an outside 
hitter to setter. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
