<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASEBALL ROUNDUP; DAVIS, CANYONS SLAM DOOR ON PIERCE, 13-9 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Johnny Davis hit a two-out grand slam in the bottom of the ninth inning 
Thursday to give College of the Canyons a 13-9 victory over Pierce in a Western 
State Conference game at Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons, which trailed, 7-0, in the second inning, chipped away at the deficit 
with a pair of runs in each of the second, third and fifth innings. 
</P>
<P>
 Pierce (18-13, 10-6 in conference play) increased its advantage to 9-6 with 
two runs in the sixth, but Canyons (11-15, 7-9) again pulled to within one with 
two runs in the bottom of the seventh. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons tied the score, 9-9, in the eighth inning when Tommy Nickels' two-out 
single drove home Davis.  
</P>
<P>
 Nickels was three for five and drove in four runs, including two with a 
second-inning homer. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Milligan of Pierce was three for four with five RBIs, including a 
three-run homer in the second inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Cuesta 9, Oxnard 6 -- Robert Sanchez went two for three and drove in a pair of 
runs, Jess Olivares went three for four, and Jason Young doubled twice and 
drove in a run for the Condors (12-16, 7-8), but it wasn't enough in a WSC game 
at Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 Joey Vargas (4-4), coming off of a 12-inning victory in his last start, took a 
4-2 lead into the seventh inning for the Condors, having scattered five hits. 
</P>
<P>
 The bottom dropped out for the knuckleball pitcher when Cuesta rallied for 
three hits and a walk to start a four-run rally. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 15, Santa Barbara 1 -- The Raiders (14-13-1, 7-7-1) scored all their 
runs in the first five innings of a WSC game at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Aaron Whitley was three for three with a home run and four RBIs.  
</P>
<P>
 Aaron Fischer had two hits including a home run and three RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 10, Santa Monica 3 -- Josh Parker (3-3) pitched his first complete 
game of the season for the Vaqueros (10-15-1, 8-7-1) in a WSC game at Santa 
Monica. 
</P>
<P>
 The sophomore left-hander struck out five, walked four, and scattered nine 
hits. 
</P>
<P>
 Armando Mesa drove in three runs for the Vaqueros in a two-for-three 
performance, and sophomore Lance Evans drove in two more runs while hitting a 
pair of doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Bakersfield 8, Valley 1 -- Bakersfield parlayed three hits, an error, two 
walks and a hit batter into a five-run fifth inning that led the Renegades to a 
WSC victory at Bakersfield. 
</P>
<P>
 Vic Seper was two for three and drove in Marlon Hamilton with the only run for 
Valley (9-15-1, 7-9) in the fifth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal Baptist 3-2, The Master's 2-4 -- Kenya Hunt hit a pair of home runs for 
The Master's during an NAIA District 3 doubleheader split at Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
 Hunt hit a two-run home run in the first game and a solo shot in the second. 
He has five home runs this season. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam Davis (3-1) picked up the victory in the second game, allowing five hits, 
two runs, striking out three and walking four in 6 2/3 innings of relief for 
the Mustangs (11-25-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Chris Beck pitched a seven-hitter and struck out 11 in the first game but took 
the loss for The Master's. 
</P>
